articles.author: Maayan Lubell, Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: What will come next remains unclear in the absence of a comprehensive agreement on the postwar future of Gaza, and although the stated aim of the ceasefire is to end the war entirely, it could easily unravel.
articles.title: Gaza ceasefire and hostage release set to begin

articles.author: Steve Holland, Tim Reid
articles.description: Trump's "Make America Great Again Victory Rally" marks his first major speech in Washington since he urged his supporters to march on the Capitol on Jan. 6, 2021, in protest against his defeat.
articles.title: Trump holds victory rally in Washington ahead of inauguration

articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: Even if temporary, the unprecedented shutdown of TikTok will have an impact on U.S.-China relations, domestic politics, the social-media marketplace and millions of Americans who depend on the app.
articles.title: TikTok goes dark for US users; Trump signals intervention

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: U.S. President Joe Biden urged despondent fellow Democrats not to give up hope as he returned to the warm embrace of South Carolina's Black churchgoing community to mark the final full day of his presidency on Sunday.
articles.title: Biden tries to lift Democrats' spirits on last full day in office

articles.author: Farah Master, David Kirton, Kevin Yao
articles.description: China's development model is at a crossroads, with a choice between much higher spending on pensions and healthcare or industrial upgrades and urbanization.
articles.title: China's ageing villages face yawning healthcare gap in fragile economy

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Nearly 81% of Indonesians approve of President Prabowo Subianto after 100 days in office, a poll showed on Monday, attributing the high rating to his early delivery on campaign promises.
articles.title: High approval rating for Indonesia's Prabowo after first 100 days, poll shows

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: South Korea's impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol has spent his first night incarcerated as a pre-trial inmate at the Seoul Detention Centre after a court issued a formal detention warrant on Sunday to hold him for up to 20 days.
articles.title: Mugshot, khaki uniform and solitary cell for South Korea's detained President Yoon

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The National Liberation Army (ELN) guerrillas are targeting community leaders and former members of a separate rebel group in the northeastern Catatumbo region, Defense Minister Ivan Velasquez said on Sunday, as local authorities said the violence has killed 80 people.
articles.title: Colombia death toll from rebel violence rises to 80

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Taiwan's premier said on Monday the government faced a crisis in day-to-day operations, including national security, because of large cuts to this year's budget proposed by opposition parties, who have cited a need to cut waste.
articles.title: Taiwan's premier says opposition's budget cuts would cripple key government functions

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Mohammed Salem
articles.description: Thousands of Palestinians burst into the streets across Gaza as a ceasefire between Israel and Hamas began on Sunday, some in celebration, others to visit the graves of relatives, while many rushed back to their homes.
articles.title: Gazans cheer as ceasefire between Israel and Hamas kicks off
